concept("graph",|cwd:///src/org/rascalmpl/library/experiments/RascalTutor/Courses/Rascal/Libraries/Vis/Figure/Figures/graph/graph.concept|,[],[],{"Library"},{},"","",""," \<ol\>\<li\> \<code\>Figure graph(Figures nodes, list[Edge] edges)\</code\>\</li\>\n\<li\> \<code\>Figure graph(FProperties, Figures nodes, list[Edge] edges)\</code\>\</li\>\n\</ol\>",{}," Takes a list of nodes and a list of edges and draws a graph. \n The nodes can be arbitrary figures that should have a name (using the id property). \n The edges determine connections between named nodes. \n \<br/\>\n\<br/\>\n\n The following constraints apply:\n \<ul\>\<li\> All nodes should have an id property with a unique value.\</li\>\n\<li\> All edges should refer to ids that are defined by the nodes.\</li\>\n\</ul\>"," \<pre class=\"listing\"\>nodes = [\n  box([id(\"A\"), size(20), fillColor(\"LightGreen\")], text(\"A\")),\n  box([id(\"B\"),  size(30), fillColor(\"LightCoral\")], text(\"B\")),\n  ellipse([id(\"C\"),  size(20), fillColor(\"LightBlue\")], text(\"C\")),\n  ellipse([id(\"D\"), size(20, 40), fillColor(\"Fuchsia\")], text(\"D\"))\n];\nedges = [ \n  edge(\"A\", \"B\"),\n  edge(\"A\", \"C\"),\n  edge(\"B\", \"C\"),\n  edge(\"C\", \"D\"),\n  edge(\"D\", \"A\")\n];    \nrender(graph([size(200)], nodes, edges));\n\</pre\> \<img  alt=\"graph 1\" src=\"Courses/Rascal/Libraries/Vis/Figure/Figures/graph/g1.png\"\>\n \<br/\>\n\<br/\>\n\n A fully connected graph of n nodes:\n \<pre class=\"listing\"\>public Figure K(int n){\n    nodes = [box([id(\"&lt;i\>\"), size(20), fillColor(\"LightBlue\")], text(\"&lt;i\>\")) | int i &lt;- [1 .. n] ];\n    edges = [[edge(\"&lt;i\>\", \"&lt;j\>\") | int j &lt;- [ 1 .. n], j != i] | int i &lt;- [ 1 .. n ] ];\n    return graph([size(300)], nodes, edges);\n}\nrender(K(20));\n\</pre\> \<img  alt=\"graph 2\" src=\"Courses/Rascal/Libraries/Vis/Figure/Figures/graph/g2.png\"\>\n \<br/\>\n\<br/\>\n\n A tree drawn using graph layout:\n \<pre class=\"listing\"\>nodes = [ \n  box([id(\"A\"), size(20), fillColor(\"green\")], text(\"A\")),\n  box([id(\"B\"), size(20), fillColor(\"red\")], text(\"B\")),\n  box([id(\"C\"), size(20), fillColor(\"blue\")], text(\"C\")),\n  box([id(\"D\"), size(20), fillColor(\"purple\")], text(\"D\")),\n  box([id(\"E\"), size(20), fillColor(\"lightblue\")], text(\"E\")),\n  box([id(\"F\"), size(20), fillColor(\"orange\")], text(\"F\")),\n  box([id(\"G\"), size(20), fillColor(\"brown\")], text(\"G\"))\n];\nedges = [ \n  edge(\"A\", \"B\"),  edge(\"A\", \"C\"),\n  edge(\"B\", \"D\"), edge(\"B\", \"E\"), \n  edge(\"C\", \"F\"),  edge(\"C\", \"G\")\t   \n];\nrender(graph([size(300)], nodes, edges));\n\</pre\> \<img  alt=\"graph 3\" src=\"Courses/Rascal/Libraries/Vis/Figure/Figures/graph/g3.png\"\>\n","","",[])